Chorology: Subcosmopolitan. Even though this chorotype well describes the present known distribution of
A . bimaculatus
, as widely reported through the literature of the nineteenth and twentieth centuries ( e.g. , Marseul 1854 ; Desbordes 1917 ;
Vienna 1980
), some authors recently pointed out that this is not its native distribution, because it was accidentally introduced in North America at various places ( Bousquet & Laplante 1999: 97 ).
